%h1#object-payment-type PaymentType

:markdown
  `PaymentType` represents how the bill is payed by; cash? or credit card?

%h2#object-payment-type-fields Fields

.row
  .span6
    %dl
      %dt= field "id", :readonly, :immutable
      %dd ID of the object.
      %dt= field "name"
      %dd Name of the payment type.
      %dt= field "position",
      %dd
        Position of the type. <code>null</code> in the case the payment methods is disabled.
      %dt= field "change"
      %dd
        <code>true</code> if customers will receive change.
      %dt= field "kind"
      %dd
        One of <code>"cash"</code>, <code>"card"</code>, or <code>"other"</code>.
        <code>"cash"</code> kind payment type exists in all accounts.

  .span6
    %pre
      = preserve do
        :escaped
          {
            "id": 111,
            "name": "Credit card",
            "position": 3,
            "change": true,
            "kind": "card",
          }


%h2#post-on-accounts-account-id-payment-types POST on /accounts/<em>account_id</em>/payment_types

:markdown
  Change payment type of the account specified by `:account_id`.

%h3 Request
.row
  .span6
    %pre
      = preserve do
        :escaped
          {
            "payment_types": [
              {
                "name": "Book Coupon",
                "change": true,
                "kind": "other"
              },
              {
                "id": 123,
                "change": false,
              }
            ]
          }
  .span6
    %dl
      %dt= field "payment_types"
      %dd
        Array of <code>PaymentType</code> objects to update/create.
        %dl
          %dt= field "id"
          %dt= field "name"
          %dt= field "change"
          %dt= field "kind"

%h3 Response
.row
  .span6
    %pre
      = preserve do
        :escaped
          {
            "timestamp": "2012-02-14T09:00:00Z",
            "payment_types" : $payment_types
          }
  .span6
    %dl
      %dt= field "timestamp"
      %dt= field "payment_types"
        